41         |   - Added OPTIONS VALIDVARNAME=V7 to force standard V7 column names
42         |     in PROC CONTENTS ODS output (prevents space-containing names
43         |     like 'Variable Number' that occur under VALIDVARNAME=ANY)
44         |   - Added space-containing column name variants to the rename map
45         |     as defense-in-depth for environments that override VALIDVARNAME:
46         |       NUM      <- VARIABLE NUMBER, VAR NUM, VAR NO
47         |       VARIABLE <- VARIABLE NAME, VAR NAME
48         |       TYPE     <- VAR TYPE, DATA TYPE, VARIABLE TYPE
49         |       LEN      <- (no space variants needed)
50         |       POS      <- POSITION, START POSITION, COLUMN POSITION, START
51         |       LABEL    <- VARIABLE LABEL, VAR LABEL
52         |   - Updated rename SQL to use SAS name literals ('name'n) for any
53         |     column names containing spaces, so PROC DATASETS RENAME works
54         |     correctly under VALIDVARNAME=ANY
55         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
56         | PURPOSE
57         | Creates a variable-level information report for all datasets in a
58         | designated directory. For each dataset the report lists variable
59         | number, name, type, length, position, and label. Results are exported to a
60         | multi-sheet Excel workbook (.xlsx) in the DAC_Documents subfolder
61         | of the output directory, with one sheet per dataset.
62         | Output columns: NUM, VARIABLE, TYPE, LEN, POS, LABEL.
63         |
64         | 1.0: REQUIRED SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited)
65         | INPUT_DIRECTORY  = Path to the folder containing SAS datasets
66         |                    (.sas7bdat) to be summarized
67         | OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = Path to the folder where the DAC_Documents
68         |                    subfolder and output file will be created.
69         |                    Must exist prior to execution.
70         |
71         | 2.0: OPTIONAL PARAMETERS
72         | None. All parameters are supplied via SYSPARM.
73         |
74         | USAGE:
75         |   sas -sysparm "input_directory|output_directory"
76         |       -sysin variable_info_cli20260320.sas
77         |
78         | OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
79         |   output_directory\
80         |   └── DAC_Documents\
81         |       └── variable_info_<GGG_PARENT>_<GG_PARENT>_<G_PARENT>_<YYYYMMDD>.xlsx
82         |           (one Excel sheet per dataset)
83         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
84         | OPERATING SYSTEM COMPATIBILITY
85         | SAS v9.4 or Higher: Yes
86         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
